top_k_tfs_per_celltype <- function(tf_df, k){
  
  # get column containing the number of cells corresponding to 10% of a celltype
  # tf_df <- tf_df %>% 
  # group_by(celltype) %>%
  # mutate(n = n()) %>% 
  # mutate(nCells = round(n * p)) %>%
  # ungroup()
  # 
  
  tf_list <- list()
  top_tfs <- list()
  
  # for each celltype get all counts for each gene
  for (i in unique(tf_df$celltype)) {
    subset <- tf_df %>% filter(celltype == i)
    celltype_tfs <- list()
    # for each gene get the number of cells in which it is expressed (count > 0)
    for (g in rownames(mat)) {
      # list to save TFs expressed in at leask x% of cells of a celltype
      total_cells <- sum(subset[g] > 0)
      if (total_cells >= subset$nCells_10[1]) {
        # append this gene to a list
        tf_list <- append(tf_list, g)
        # add tf to the list for this celltype
        celltype_tfs <- append(celltype_tfs, g)
        
      # for the TFs expressed in at least x% of cells of this celltype
      # get the top k expressed TFs
      topk_df <- subset %>% 
        select(unlist(celltype_tfs)) %>%
        summarise(across(.cols = everything(), mean)) %>%
        pivot_longer(cols = everything()) %>% 
        slice_max(order_by = value, n = k)
      
      top_tfs[[i]] = list(names = topk_df$name, values = topk_df$value)
      }
    }
  }
  return(list(top_tfs, unique(tf_list)))
}
